  "texts": [
    {
      "key": "plugin.title",
      "source": "車両ぷらぐいん",
      "translation": "Vehicle Plugin"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{001D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.name",
      "source": "国鉄特急色",
      "translation": "JNR Limited Express Livery"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{001D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.company",
      "source": "JR東日本",
      "translation": "JR East"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{001D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.type",
      "source": "183系0番台",
      "translation": "183 Series 0"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{001D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.description",
      "source": "内房線，外房線の電化と、総武線の東京地下駅へ乗入れるため製造された車両。",
      "translation": "Rolling stock manufactured for the electrification of the Uchibo and Sotobo Lines and for through-service to the Tokyo underground station on the Sobu Line."
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{002D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.name",
      "source": "国鉄特急色",
      "translation": "JNR Limited Express Livery"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{002D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.company",
      "source": "JR東海",
      "translation": "JR Central"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{002D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.type",
      "source": "381系",
      "translation": "381 Series"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{002D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.description",
      "source": "カーブの多い区間での到達時間短縮を図るために製造された自然振り子式電車。\n重心を下げるためクーラーが床下に搭載されており、屋根上が非常にすっきりしている。\n「しなの」「くろしお」「やくも」に投入された。",
      "translation": "A natural pendulum-type electric train manufactured to shorten travel times on winding sections. To lower the center of gravity, the air conditioner is mounted under the floor, leaving the roof very clean. Introduced on the 'Shinano', 'Kuroshio', and 'Yakumo' services."
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{002D31EF-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.name",
      "source": "国鉄特急色",
      "translation": "JNR Limited Express Livery"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{002D31EF-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.company",
      "source": "JR西日本",
      "translation": "JR West"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{002D31EF-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.type",
      "source": "381系",
      "translation": "381 Series"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{002D31EF-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.description",
      "source": "カーブの多い区間での到達時間短縮を図るために製造された自然振り子式電車。\n重心を下げるためクーラーが床下に搭載されており、屋根上が非常にすっきりしている。\n「しなの」「くろしお」「やくも」に投入された。",
      "translation": "A natural pendulum-type electric train manufactured to shorten travel times on winding sections. To lower the center of gravity, the air conditioner is mounted under the floor, leaving the roof very clean. Introduced on the 'Shinano', 'Kuroshio', and 'Yakumo' services."
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{003D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.name",
      "source": "くろしお色",
      "translation": "Kuroshio livery"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{003D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.company",
      "source": "JR西日本",
      "translation": "JR West"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{003D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.type",
      "source": "381系",
      "translation": "381 Series"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{003D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.description",
      "source": "「くろしお」用の381系は、283系「オーシャンアロー」にあわせた塗色に変更されている。",
      "translation": "The 381 Series for 'Kuroshio' has been repainted to match the 283 Series 'Ocean Arrow' livery."
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{004D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.name",
      "source": "やくも色",
      "translation": "Yakumo Color"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{004D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.company",
      "source": "JR西日本",
      "translation": "JR West"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{004D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.type",
      "source": "381系",
      "translation": "381 Series"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{004D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.description",
      "source": "「やくも」用の381系グレードアップ車。伯備線の陰陽連絡特急である「やくも」は、「スーパーやくも」を含め本数は多いが、中には3両編成の運転もある。",
      "translation": "The 381 Series upgraded cars for 'Yakumo'. The 'Yakumo' limited express, connecting San'in and Sanyo regions via the Hakubi Line, has many services including 'Super Yakumo', with some operating as 3-car formations."
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{005D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.name",
      "source": "あさま色",
      "translation": "Asama Livery"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{005D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.company",
      "source": "JR東日本",
      "translation": "JR East"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{005D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.type",
      "source": "189系",
      "translation": "189 Series"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{005D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.description",
      "source": "新幹線になる前の「あさま」で使用されていた車両。189系は碓氷峠で機関車との協調運転が可能な形式である。",
      "translation": "Vehicles used for the 'Asama' before the Shinkansen era. The 189 series is a type capable of cooperative operation with locomotives on the Usui Pass."
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{006D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.company",
      "source": "JR西日本",
      "translation": "JR West"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{006D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.type",
      "source": "183系800番台",
      "translation": "183 Series 800"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{006D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.description",
      "source": "京都、大阪方面と、近畿北部を結ぶ、「北近畿」等に使われている車両。\nもともとは485系で交流機器を撤去し183系になった。",
      "translation": "Rolling stock used for \"Kitakinki\" and other services connecting Kyoto and Osaka with northern Kinki. Originally 485 Series, they became 183 Series after AC equipment was removed."
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{007D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.name",
      "source": "あずさ色",
      "translation": "Azusa Livery"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{007D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.company",
      "source": "JR東日本",
      "translation": "JR East"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{007D31EE-F3A2-4CD6-A820-54200A6EF537}.type",
      "source": "183系1000番台",
      "translation": "183 Series 1000"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD280-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.name",
      "source": "（スラントノーズタイプ）",
      "translation": "(Slant Nose Type)"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD280-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.company",
      "source": "JR北海道",
      "translation": "JR Hokkaido"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD280-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.type",
      "source": "キハ183-0番台",
      "translation": "Kiha 183-0 Series"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD280-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.description",
      "source": "北海道用として製造された特急型気動車。\n現在は〈オホーツク〉などで使用されている。",
      "translation": "A limited express diesel railcar manufactured for use in Hokkaido. Currently used for services such as the 'Okhotsk'."
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD281-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.name",
      "source": "南風等",
      "translation": "Nanpu, etc."
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD281-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.company",
      "source": "JR四国",
      "translation": "JR Shikoku"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD281-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.type",
      "source": "2000系",
      "translation": "2000 Series"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD281-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.description",
      "source": "世界初の振子式気動車であり、日本初の制御付振子車両。\nこの車両の開発で完成された技術が各地の列車の高速化に貢献している。",
      "translation": "The world's first tilting diesel railcar and Japan's first controlled-tilt vehicle. The technology perfected in the development of this vehicle has contributed to the high-speed operation of trains in various regions."
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD282-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.name",
      "source": "サンライズエクスプレス",
      "translation": "Sunrise Express"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD282-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.company",
      "source": "JR西日本",
      "translation": "JR West"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD282-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.type",
      "source": "285系",
      "translation": "285 Series"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD282-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.description",
      "source": "1998年、〈出雲〉と〈瀬戸〉に登場した寝台特急電車。\n寝台設備はすべて個室となっている。",
      "translation": "A limited express sleeper electric train introduced in 1998 for the Izumo and Seto services. All sleeping accommodations are private rooms."
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD283-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.name",
      "source": "サンライズエクスプレス",
      "translation": "Sunrise Express"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD283-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.company",
      "source": "JR東海",
      "translation": "JR Central"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD283-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.type",
      "source": "285系",
      "translation": "285 Series"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD283-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.description",
      "source": "1998年、〈出雲〉と〈瀬戸〉に登場した寝台特急電車。\n寝台設備はすべて個室となっている。",
      "translation": "A limited express sleeper electric train introduced in 1998 for the Izumo and Seto services. All sleeping accommodations are private rooms."
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD284-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.company",
      "source": "JR西日本",
      "translation": "JR West"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD284-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.type",
      "source": "300系",
      "translation": "300 Series"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD284-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.description",
      "source": "最高速度270km/h、東京－新大阪を2時間半で走る〈のぞみ〉の運転開始に向けてJR東海が開発した車両。\nJR東海のJ編成16両61本と、JR西日本のF編成16両9本が存在する。",
      "translation": "A train developed by JR Central for the start of the <Nozomi> service, running at a maximum speed of 270 km/h and connecting Tokyo and Shin-Osaka in 2.5 hours. There are 61 J-sets of 16 cars from JR Central and 9 F-sets of 16 cars from JR West."
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD285-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.company",
      "source": "JR東海",
      "translation": "JR Central"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD285-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.type",
      "source": "300系",
      "translation": "300 Series"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD285-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.description",
      "source": "最高速度270km/h、東京－新大阪を2時間半で走る〈のぞみ〉の運転開始に向けてJR東海が開発した車両。\nJR東海のJ編成16両61本と、JR西日本のF編成16両9本が存在する。",
      "translation": "A train developed by JR Central for the start of the <Nozomi> service, running at a maximum speed of 270 km/h and connecting Tokyo and Shin-Osaka in 2.5 hours. There are 61 J-sets of 16 cars from JR Central and 9 F-sets of 16 cars from JR West."
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD286-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.name",
      "source": "成田エクスプレス",
      "translation": "Narita Express"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD286-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.company",
      "source": "JR東日本",
      "translation": "JR East"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD286-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.type",
      "source": "253系",
      "translation": "253 Series"
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD286-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.description",
      "source": "成田空港と都心を結ぶ特急〈成田エクスプレス〉専用車両。\n当初基本編成は3両だったが、後に需要に合わせて6両編成も登場している。",
      "translation": "Dedicated limited express train for the Narita Express, connecting Narita Airport and the city center. Initially, the basic formation was 3 cars, but later 6-car formations also appeared to meet demand."
    },
    {
      "key": "contribution.{FBEAD293-1069-11D7-AA41-000740323A8D}.name",
      "source": "首都圏色",
      "translation": "Metropolitan Area Color"
    },
    {
